
‡¶∏‡¶´‡¶ü‡¶ì‡ßü‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶∞ ‡¶°‡ßá‡¶≠‡ßá‡¶≤‡¶™‡¶æ‡¶∞ ‡¶π‡¶ø‡¶∏‡ßá‡¶¨‡ßá ‡¶ü‡¶ø‡¶™‡¶∏:
‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶Ç‡¶ï‡¶ø‡¶Ç ‡¶∏‡¶´‡¶ü‡¶ì‡ßü‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶∞ ‡¶°‡ßá‡¶≠‡ßá‡¶≤‡¶™‡¶æ‡¶∞ ‡¶π‡¶ø‡¶∏‡ßá‡¶¨‡ßá ‡¶Ü‡¶™‡¶®‡¶æ‡¶∞ ‡¶ú‡¶®‡ßç‡¶Ø Double Entry Accounting ‡¶è‡¶¨‡¶Ç Debit/Credit ‡¶è‡¶∞ ‡¶ï‡¶®‡¶∏‡ßá‡¶™‡ßç‡¶ü‡¶ü‡¶ø ‡¶™‡¶æ‡¶®‡¶ø‡¶∞ ‡¶Æ‡¶§‡ßã ‡¶™‡¶∞‡¶ø‡¶∑‡ßç‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶∞ ‡¶π‡¶ì‡ßü‡¶æ ‡¶ú‡¶∞‡ßÅ‡¶∞‡¶ø‡•§ 
‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶∞‡¶£ ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶Ç‡¶ï‡¶ø‡¶Ç ‡¶°‡¶æ‡¶ü‡¶æ‡¶¨‡ßá‡¶∏‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶Æ‡ßÇ‡¶≤ ‡¶≠‡¶ø‡¶§‡ßç‡¶§‡¶ø‡¶á ‡¶π‡¶≤‡ßã ‡¶è‡¶ü‡¶ø‡•§

‡¶Ü‡¶™‡¶®‡¶ø ‡¶Ø‡¶ñ‡¶® ‡¶ï‡ßã‡¶° ‡¶≤‡¶ø‡¶ñ‡¶¨‡ßá‡¶®, ‡¶§‡¶ñ‡¶® ‡¶á‡¶â‡¶ú‡¶æ‡¶∞ ‡¶¨‡¶æ ‡¶ó‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶æ‡¶π‡¶ï‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶¶‡¶ø‡¶ï ‡¶•‡ßá‡¶ï‡ßá ‡¶ö‡¶ø‡¶®‡ßç‡¶§‡¶æ ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡¶¨‡ßá‡¶® ‡¶®‡¶æ, 
‡¶ö‡¶ø‡¶®‡ßç‡¶§‡¶æ ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡¶¨‡ßá‡¶® ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶Ç‡¶ï‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶≤‡ßá‡¶ú‡¶æ‡¶∞ (Ledger) ‡¶è‡¶∞ ‡¶¶‡¶ø‡¶ï ‡¶•‡ßá‡¶ï‡ßá‡•§ 

‡¶®‡¶ø‡¶ö‡ßá ‡¶∏‡¶π‡¶ú ‡¶â‡¶¶‡¶æ‡¶π‡¶∞‡¶£‡¶∏‡¶π ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶ñ‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡¶æ ‡¶π‡¶≤‡ßã:

---

## ‡ßß. Double Entry Accounting (‡¶¶‡ßÅ-‡¶§‡¶∞‡¶´‡¶æ ‡¶¶‡¶æ‡¶ñ‡¶ø‡¶≤‡¶æ ‡¶™‡¶¶‡ßç‡¶ß‡¶§‡¶ø)

‡¶è‡¶á ‡¶™‡¶¶‡ßç‡¶ß‡¶§‡¶ø‡¶∞ ‡¶Æ‡ßÇ‡¶≤ ‡¶ï‡¶•‡¶æ ‡¶π‡¶≤‡ßã‚Äî ‡¶™‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶§‡¶ø‡¶ü‡¶ø ‡¶≤‡ßá‡¶®‡¶¶‡ßá‡¶®‡ßá‡¶∞ (Transaction) ‡¶ï‡¶Æ‡¶™‡¶ï‡ßç‡¶∑‡ßá ‡¶¶‡ßÅ‡¶ü‡¶ø ‡¶™‡¶ï‡ßç‡¶∑ ‡¶•‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶¨‡ßá‡•§ 
‡¶è‡¶ï ‡¶™‡¶ï‡ßç‡¶∑ ‡¶•‡ßá‡¶ï‡ßá ‡¶ü‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶æ ‡¶¨‡¶æ ‡¶∏‡ßÅ‡¶¨‡¶ø‡¶ß‡¶æ ‡¶¨‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶π‡¶¨‡ßá, ‡¶Ö‡¶®‡ßç‡¶Ø ‡¶™‡¶ï‡ßç‡¶∑‡ßá ‡¶∏‡ßá‡¶ü‡¶ø ‡¶ú‡¶Æ‡¶æ ‡¶π‡¶¨‡ßá‡•§

‡¶∏‡¶´‡¶ü‡¶ì‡ßü‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶∞ ‡¶á‡¶û‡ßç‡¶ú‡¶ø‡¶®‡¶ø‡ßü‡¶æ‡¶∞‡¶ø‡¶Ç‡ßü‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶≠‡¶æ‡¶∑‡¶æ‡ßü ‡¶¨‡¶≤‡¶≤‡ßá: 
‡¶Ü‡¶™‡¶®‡¶æ‡¶∞ ‡¶°‡¶æ‡¶ü‡¶æ‡¶¨‡ßá‡¶∏‡ßá ‡¶è‡¶ï‡¶ü‡¶ø ‡¶è‡¶®‡ßç‡¶ü‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶ø ‡¶π‡¶¨‡ßá ‡¶®‡¶æ, ‡¶¨‡¶∞‡¶Ç ‡¶è‡¶ï‡¶∏‡¶æ‡¶•‡ßá ‡¶¶‡ßÅ‡¶ü‡¶ø ‡¶è‡¶®‡ßç‡¶ü‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶ø ‡¶π‡¶¨‡ßá (‡¶è‡¶ï‡¶ü‡¶ø Debit ‡¶è‡¶¨‡¶Ç ‡¶è‡¶ï‡¶ü‡¶ø Credit)‡•§
‡¶¶‡¶ø‡¶®‡¶∂‡ßá‡¶∑‡ßá ‡¶∏‡¶¨ Debit ‡¶è‡¶¨‡¶Ç ‡¶∏‡¶¨ Credit ‡¶è‡¶∞ ‡¶Ø‡ßã‡¶ó‡¶´‡¶≤ ‡¶∏‡¶¨‡¶∏‡¶Æ‡ßü ‡¶∏‡¶Æ‡¶æ‡¶® (=) ‡¶π‡¶§‡ßá ‡¶π‡¶¨‡ßá‡•§

### ‡¶ó‡¶æ‡¶£‡¶ø‡¶§‡¶ø‡¶ï ‡¶∏‡ßÇ‡¶§‡ßç‡¶∞ (Accounting Equation):

---

## ‡ß®. Debit / Credit ‡¶è‡¶∞ ‡¶ó‡ßã‡¶≤‡ßç‡¶°‡ßá‡¶® ‡¶∞‡ßÅ‡¶≤‡¶∏ (‡¶∏‡¶π‡¶ú‡¶≠‡¶æ‡¶¨‡ßá)

‡¶Ö‡¶®‡ßá‡¶ï‡ßá ‡¶Æ‡¶®‡ßá ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡ßá‡¶® Debit ‡¶Æ‡¶æ‡¶®‡ßá‡¶á ‡¶Ø‡ßã‡¶ó ‡¶Ü‡¶∞ Credit ‡¶Æ‡¶æ‡¶®‡ßá‡¶á ‡¶¨‡¶ø‡ßü‡ßã‡¶ó‡•§ 
‡¶ï‡¶ø‡¶®‡ßç‡¶§‡ßÅ ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶Ç‡¶ï‡¶ø‡¶Ç‡ßü‡ßá ‡¶è‡¶ü‡¶ø ‡¶®‡¶ø‡¶∞‡ßç‡¶≠‡¶∞ ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡ßá ‡¶Ü‡¶™‡¶®‡¶ø ‡¶ï‡ßã‡¶® ‡¶ß‡¶∞‡¶£‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶Ö‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶â‡¶®‡ßç‡¶ü‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶∏‡¶æ‡¶•‡ßá ‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶ú ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡¶õ‡ßá‡¶® ‡¶§‡¶æ‡¶∞ ‡¶ì‡¶™‡¶∞‡•§

‡¶Ü‡¶™‡¶®‡¶ø ‡¶Ø‡¶ñ‡¶® ‡¶ï‡ßã‡¶° ‡¶≤‡¶ø‡¶ñ‡¶¨‡ßá‡¶®,
‡¶§‡¶ñ‡¶® ‡¶á‡¶â‡¶ú‡¶æ‡¶∞ ‡¶¨‡¶æ ‡¶ó‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶æ‡¶π‡¶ï‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶¶‡¶ø‡¶ï ‡¶•‡ßá‡¶ï‡ßá ‡¶ö‡¶ø‡¶®‡ßç‡¶§‡¶æ ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡¶¨‡ßá‡¶® ‡¶®‡¶æ, ‡¶ö‡¶ø‡¶®‡ßç‡¶§‡¶æ ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡¶¨‡ßá‡¶® ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶Ç‡¶ï‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶≤‡ßá‡¶ú‡¶æ‡¶∞ (Ledger) ‡¶è‡¶∞ ‡¶¶‡¶ø‡¶ï ‡¶•‡ßá‡¶ï‡ßá‡•§ 

üè¶ ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶Ç‡¶ï‡ßá ‡¶ï‡ßã‡¶® ‡¶ï‡ßã‡¶® ‡¶Ö‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶â‡¶®‡ßç‡¶ü‡ßá ‡¶°‡¶æ‡¶¨‡¶≤ ‡¶è‡¶®‡ßç‡¶ü‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶ø ‡¶π‡ßü?
        üí∞ Cash / Bank Balance    üë§ Customer Deposit
        üè¶ Loan Account           üíµ Interest Income
        üßæ Expense Account

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| ‡¶Ö‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶â‡¶®‡ßç‡¶ü‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶ß‡¶∞‡¶£                          | ‡¶¨‡ßÉ‡¶¶‡ßç‡¶ß‡¶ø ‡¶™‡ßá‡¶≤‡ßá (Increase)   | ‡¶π‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶æ‡¶∏ ‡¶™‡ßá‡¶≤‡ßá (Decrease) |
| --------------------------------------- | ----------------------| -------------------- |
| Assets (‡¶∏‡¶Æ‡ßç‡¶™‡¶¶): ‡¶Ø‡ßá‡¶Æ‡¶® ‡¶ï‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶∂, ‡¶≤‡ßã‡¶®         | Debit                 | Credit               |
| Liabilities (‡¶¶‡¶æ‡ßü): ‡¶Ø‡ßá‡¶Æ‡¶® ‡¶ó‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶æ‡¶π‡¶ï‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶Ü‡¶Æ‡¶æ‡¶®‡¶§  | Credit                | Debit                |
| Income (‡¶Ü‡ßü): ‡¶Ø‡ßá‡¶Æ‡¶® ‡¶ö‡¶æ‡¶∞‡ßç‡¶ú ‡¶¨‡¶æ ‡¶≤‡¶æ‡¶≠          | Credit                | Debit                |
| Expense (‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡ßü): ‡¶Ø‡ßá‡¶Æ‡¶® ‡¶∏‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶≤‡¶æ‡¶∞‡¶ø ‡¶¨‡¶æ ‡¶á‡¶â‡¶ü‡¶ø‡¶≤‡¶ø‡¶ü‡¶ø   | Debit                 | Credit               |
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------



‡¶Ö‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶â‡¶®‡ßç‡¶ü‡¶ø‡¶Ç‡ßü‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶è‡¶á ‡¶ö‡¶æ‡¶∞‡ßç‡¶ü‡¶ü‡¶ø ‡¶Æ‡ßÅ‡¶ñ‡¶∏‡ßç‡¶• ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡¶æ‡¶∞ ‡¶ö‡ßá‡ßü‡ßá ‡¶≤‡¶ú‡¶ø‡¶ï ‡¶¨‡¶æ ‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶∞‡¶£ ‡¶¶‡¶ø‡ßü‡ßá ‡¶¨‡ßÅ‡¶ù‡¶≤‡ßá ‡¶Ü‡¶™‡¶®‡¶æ‡¶∞ ‡¶ú‡¶®‡ßç‡¶Ø ‡¶ï‡ßã‡¶°‡¶ø‡¶Ç ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡¶æ ‡¶Ö‡¶®‡ßá‡¶ï ‡¶∏‡¶π‡¶ú ‡¶π‡¶¨‡ßá‡•§ 
‡¶Æ‡¶®‡ßá ‡¶∞‡¶æ‡¶ñ‡¶¨‡ßá‡¶®, ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶Ç‡¶ï ‡¶®‡¶ø‡¶ú‡ßá‡¶ï‡ßá ‡¶è‡¶ï‡¶ü‡¶ø "‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶ï‡ßç‡¶§‡¶ø" ‡¶Æ‡¶®‡ßá ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡ßá ‡¶è‡¶¨‡¶Ç ‡¶∏‡¶¨ ‡¶π‡¶ø‡¶∏‡¶æ‡¶¨ ‡¶®‡¶ø‡¶ú‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶™‡¶ï‡ßá‡¶ü ‡¶¨‡¶æ ‡¶≠‡¶≤‡ßç‡¶ü‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶∏‡¶æ‡¶™‡ßá‡¶ï‡ßç‡¶∑‡ßá ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡ßá‡•§

‡¶®‡¶ø‡¶ö‡ßá ‡¶¨‡¶æ‡¶∏‡ßç‡¶§‡¶¨ ‡¶â‡¶¶‡¶æ‡¶π‡¶∞‡¶£‡¶∏‡¶π ‡¶ï‡ßá‡¶® ‡¶è‡¶ó‡ßÅ‡¶≤‡ßã ‡¶°‡ßá‡¶¨‡¶ø‡¶ü ‡¶Ü‡¶∞ ‡¶ï‡ßç‡¶∞‡ßá‡¶°‡¶ø‡¶ü ‡¶π‡ßü ‡¶§‡¶æ ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶ñ‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡¶æ ‡¶π‡¶≤‡ßã:

---

### ‡ßß. Assets (‡¶∏‡¶Æ‡ßç‡¶™‡¶¶) ‚Äî ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶Ç‡¶ï‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶Ø‡¶æ ‡¶®‡¶ø‡¶ú‡ßá‡¶∞

‡¶≤‡¶ú‡¶ø‡¶ï: 
‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶Ç‡¶ï‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶≠‡¶≤‡ßç‡¶ü‡ßá ‡¶Ø‡¶ñ‡¶® ‡¶®‡¶§‡ßÅ‡¶® ‡¶ï‡¶ø‡¶õ‡ßÅ ‡¶Ü‡¶∏‡ßá (‡¶Ø‡ßá‡¶Æ‡¶® ‡¶ï‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶∂), ‡¶§‡¶ñ‡¶® ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶Ç‡¶ï‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶∏‡¶Æ‡ßç‡¶™‡¶¶ ‡¶¨‡¶æ‡ßú‡ßá‡•§ ‡¶Ü‡¶∞ ‡¶∏‡¶Æ‡ßç‡¶™‡¶¶ ‡¶¨‡¶æ‡ßú‡¶≤‡ßá ‡¶∏‡ßá‡¶ü‡¶æ‡¶ï‡ßá ‡¶¨‡¶æ‡¶Æ ‡¶¶‡¶ø‡¶ï‡ßá (Debit) ‡¶≤‡ßá‡¶ñ‡¶æ ‡¶π‡ßü‡•§

- ‡¶¨‡¶æ‡¶∏‡ßç‡¶§‡¶¨ ‡¶â‡¶¶‡¶æ‡¶π‡¶∞‡¶£: ‡¶Ü‡¶™‡¶®‡¶ø ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶Ç‡¶ï‡ßá ‡ß´,‡ß¶‡ß¶‡ß¶ ‡¶ü‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶æ ‡¶ú‡¶Æ‡¶æ ‡¶¶‡¶ø‡¶≤‡ßá‡¶®‡•§ ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶Ç‡¶ï‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶™‡¶ï‡ßá‡¶ü‡ßá (‡¶≠‡¶≤‡ßç‡¶ü‡ßá) ‡ß´,‡ß¶‡ß¶‡ß¶ ‡¶ü‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶æ ‡¶®‡¶ó‡¶¶ ‡¶ï‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶∂ ‡¶¨‡¶æ‡ßú‡¶≤‡ßã‡•§
- ‡¶ò‡¶ü‡¶®‡¶æ: ‡¶∏‡¶Æ‡ßç‡¶™‡¶¶ ‡¶¨‡ßÉ‡¶¶‡ßç‡¶ß‡¶ø‡•§
- ‡¶Ö‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶∂‡¶®: Debit Cash Account.

| ‡¶Ö‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶â‡¶®‡ßç‡¶ü   | Debit (‡¶°‡ßá‡¶¨‡¶ø‡¶ü) | Credit (‡¶ï‡ßç‡¶∞‡ßá‡¶°‡¶ø‡¶ü) |
| ------------ | ------------- | ---------------- |
| Cash Account | 5,000         | ‚Äî                |



- ‡¶π‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶æ‡¶∏ ‡¶™‡¶æ‡¶ì‡ßü‡¶æ‡¶∞ ‡¶â‡¶¶‡¶æ‡¶π‡¶∞‡¶£: ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶Ç‡¶ï ‡¶∏‡ßá‡¶á ‡¶ü‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶æ ‡¶•‡ßá‡¶ï‡ßá ‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶â‡¶ï‡ßá ‡¶≤‡ßã‡¶® ‡¶¶‡¶ø‡¶≤‡ßã ‡¶¨‡¶æ ‡¶ñ‡¶∞‡¶ö ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡¶≤‡ßã‡•§ ‡¶≠‡¶≤‡ßç‡¶ü ‡¶•‡ßá‡¶ï‡ßá ‡¶ï‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶∂ ‡¶ö‡¶≤‡ßá ‡¶ó‡ßá‡¶≤‡•§
- ‡¶ò‡¶ü‡¶®‡¶æ: ‡¶∏‡¶Æ‡ßç‡¶™‡¶¶ ‡¶π‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶æ‡¶∏‡•§
- ‡¶Ö‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶∂‡¶®: Credit Cash Account.

| ‡¶Ö‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶â‡¶®‡ßç‡¶ü   | Debit (‡¶°‡ßá‡¶¨‡¶ø‡¶ü) | Credit (‡¶ï‡ßç‡¶∞‡ßá‡¶°‡¶ø‡¶ü) |
| ------------ | ------------- | ---------------- |
| Cash Account | ‚Äî             | 5,000            |



---

### ‡ß®. Liabilities (‡¶¶‡¶æ‡ßü) ‚Äî ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶Ç‡¶ï ‡¶Ø‡¶æ ‡¶Ö‡¶®‡ßç‡¶Ø‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶õ‡ßá ‡¶ã‡¶£‡ßÄ

‡¶≤‡¶ú‡¶ø‡¶ï: 
‡¶ó‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶æ‡¶π‡¶ï‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶Ü‡¶Æ‡¶æ‡¶®‡¶§ (Deposit) ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶Ç‡¶ï‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶õ‡ßá ‡¶è‡¶ï‡¶ü‡¶æ "‡¶¶‡¶æ‡ßü"‡•§ 
‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶∞‡¶£ ‡¶ó‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶æ‡¶π‡¶ï ‡¶Ü‡¶ú ‡¶ü‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶æ ‡¶∞‡¶æ‡¶ñ‡¶≤‡ßá‡¶ì ‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶≤ ‡¶∏‡ßá‡¶ü‡¶æ ‡¶´‡ßá‡¶∞‡¶§ ‡¶ö‡¶æ‡¶á‡¶¨‡ßá‡•§ ‡¶¶‡¶æ‡ßü ‡¶¨‡¶æ‡ßú‡¶≤‡ßá ‡¶∏‡ßá‡¶ü‡¶æ ‡¶°‡¶æ‡¶® ‡¶¶‡¶ø‡¶ï‡ßá (Credit) ‡¶≤‡ßá‡¶ñ‡¶æ ‡¶π‡ßü‡•§

- ‡¶¨‡¶æ‡¶∏‡ßç‡¶§‡¶¨ ‡¶â‡¶¶‡¶æ‡¶π‡¶∞‡¶£: ‡¶Ü‡¶™‡¶®‡¶ø ‡¶Ø‡¶ñ‡¶® ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶Ç‡¶ï‡ßá ‡ß´,‡ß¶‡ß¶‡ß¶ ‡¶ü‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶æ ‡¶ú‡¶Æ‡¶æ ‡¶¶‡¶ø‡¶≤‡ßá‡¶®, ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶Ç‡¶ï ‡¶ñ‡ßÅ‡¶∂‡¶ø ‡¶π‡¶ì‡ßü‡¶æ‡¶∞ ‡¶¨‡¶¶‡¶≤‡ßá ‡¶ö‡¶ø‡¶®‡ßç‡¶§‡¶ø‡¶§ ‡¶π‡ßü‚Äî ‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶∞‡¶£ ‡¶§‡¶æ‡¶ï‡ßá ‡¶è‡¶á ‡ß´,‡ß¶‡ß¶‡ß¶ ‡¶ü‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶æ ‡¶Ü‡¶™‡¶®‡¶æ‡¶ï‡ßá ‡¶´‡ßá‡¶∞‡¶§ ‡¶¶‡¶ø‡¶§‡ßá ‡¶π‡¶¨‡ßá‡•§ ‡¶§‡¶æ‡¶∞ "‡¶¶‡¶æ‡ßü" ‡¶¨‡¶æ‡ßú‡¶≤‡ßã‡•§
- ‡¶ò‡¶ü‡¶®‡¶æ: ‡¶¶‡¶æ‡ßü ‡¶¨‡ßÉ‡¶¶‡ßç‡¶ß‡¶ø‡•§
- ‡¶Ö‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶∂‡¶®:  Debit Bank Account but  Credit Customer Account. (‡¶è‡¶á‡¶ú‡¶®‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶á ‡¶Ü‡¶™‡¶®‡¶æ‡¶∞ ‡¶´‡ßã‡¶®‡ßá SMS ‡¶Ü‡¶∏‡ßá: "Your account has been Credited")

| ‡¶Ö‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶â‡¶®‡ßç‡¶ü                   | Debit (‡¶°‡ßá‡¶¨‡¶ø‡¶ü) | Credit (‡¶ï‡ßç‡¶∞‡ßá‡¶°‡¶ø‡¶ü) |
| ---------------------------- | ------------- | ---------------- |
| Cash (Bank Asset)            | 5,000         | ‚Äî                |
| Customer Deposit (Liability) | ‚Äî             | 5,000            |




- ‡¶π‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶æ‡¶∏ ‡¶™‡¶æ‡¶ì‡ßü‡¶æ‡¶∞ ‡¶â‡¶¶‡¶æ‡¶π‡¶∞‡¶£: ‡¶Ü‡¶™‡¶®‡¶ø ‡¶Ü‡¶™‡¶®‡¶æ‡¶∞ ‡¶è‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶â‡¶®‡ßç‡¶ü ‡¶•‡ßá‡¶ï‡ßá ‡ßß,‡ß¶‡ß¶‡ß¶ ‡¶ü‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶æ ‡¶§‡ßÅ‡¶≤‡ßá ‡¶®‡¶ø‡¶≤‡ßá‡¶®‡•§ ‡¶è‡¶ñ‡¶® ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶Ç‡¶ï‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶¶‡¶æ‡ßü ‡ßß,‡ß¶‡ß¶‡ß¶ ‡¶ü‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶æ ‡¶ï‡¶Æ‡ßá ‡¶ó‡ßá‡¶≤‡•§
- ‡¶ò‡¶ü‡¶®‡¶æ: ‡¶¶‡¶æ‡ßü ‡¶π‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶æ‡¶∏‡•§
- ‡¶Ö‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶∂‡¶®: Credit Bank Account but Debit Customer Account.

| ‡¶Ö‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶â‡¶®‡ßç‡¶ü                   | Debit (‡¶°‡ßá‡¶¨‡¶ø‡¶ü) | Credit (‡¶ï‡ßç‡¶∞‡ßá‡¶°‡¶ø‡¶ü) |
| ---------------------------- | ------------- | ---------------- |
| Customer Deposit (Liability) | 1,000         | ‚Äî                |
| Cash (Bank Asset)            | ‚Äî             | 1,000            |



---

### ‡ß©. Income (‡¶Ü‡ßü) ‚Äî ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶Ç‡¶ï‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶™‡¶ï‡ßá‡¶ü‡ßá ‡¶Ø‡¶æ ‡¶¢‡ßÅ‡¶ï‡¶õ‡ßá

‡¶≤‡¶ú‡¶ø‡¶ï: 
‡¶Ü‡ßü ‡¶π‡¶≤‡ßá ‡¶Ü‡¶≤‡ßç‡¶ü‡¶ø‡¶Æ‡ßá‡¶ü‡¶≤‡¶ø ‡¶∏‡ßá‡¶ü‡¶æ ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶Ç‡¶ï‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶Æ‡ßÇ‡¶≤‡¶ß‡¶® ‡¶¨‡¶æ ‡¶¶‡¶æ‡ßü (Equity) ‡¶¨‡¶æ‡ßú‡¶æ‡ßü, ‡¶§‡¶æ‡¶á ‡¶Ü‡ßü‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶®‡¶ø‡ßü‡¶Æ ‡¶¶‡¶æ‡ßü‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶Æ‡¶§‡ßã‡¶á‡•§ ‡¶Ü‡ßü ‡¶¨‡¶æ‡ßú‡¶≤‡ßá Credit ‡¶π‡ßü‡•§

- ‡¶¨‡¶æ‡¶∏‡ßç‡¶§‡¶¨ ‡¶â‡¶¶‡¶æ‡¶π‡¶∞‡¶£: ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶Ç‡¶ï ‡¶Ü‡¶™‡¶®‡¶æ‡¶∞ ‡¶è‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶â‡¶®‡ßç‡¶ü ‡¶•‡ßá‡¶ï‡ßá ‡¶¨‡¶æ‡ßé‡¶∏‡¶∞‡¶ø‡¶ï ‡ß´‡ß¶‡ß¶ ‡¶ü‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶æ ‡¶ö‡¶æ‡¶∞‡ßç‡¶ú ‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶ü‡¶≤‡ßã‡•§ ‡¶è‡¶ü‡¶æ ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶Ç‡¶ï‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶Ü‡ßü‡•§
- ‡¶ò‡¶ü‡¶®‡¶æ: ‡¶Ü‡ßü ‡¶¨‡ßÉ‡¶¶‡ßç‡¶ß‡¶ø‡•§
- ‡¶Ö‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶∂‡¶®: Credit Service Charge Income Account.

| ‡¶Ö‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶â‡¶®‡ßç‡¶ü            | Debit (‡¶°‡ßá‡¶¨‡¶ø‡¶ü) | Credit (‡¶ï‡ßç‡¶∞‡ßá‡¶°‡¶ø‡¶ü) |
| --------------------- | ------------- | ---------------- |
| Service Charge Income | ‚Äî             | 500              |


- ‡¶π‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶æ‡¶∏ ‡¶™‡¶æ‡¶ì‡ßü‡¶æ‡¶∞ ‡¶â‡¶¶‡¶æ‡¶π‡¶∞‡¶£: ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶Ç‡¶ï ‡¶≠‡ßÅ‡¶≤ ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡ßá ‡¶¨‡ßá‡¶∂‡¶ø ‡¶ö‡¶æ‡¶∞‡ßç‡¶ú ‡¶ï‡ßá‡¶ü‡ßá ‡¶´‡ßá‡¶≤‡ßá‡¶õ‡¶ø‡¶≤, ‡¶è‡¶ñ‡¶® ‡¶∏‡ßá‡¶ü‡¶æ ‡¶´‡ßá‡¶∞‡¶§ ‡¶¶‡¶ø‡ßü‡ßá ‡¶¶‡¶ø‡¶≤‡ßã‡•§
- ‡¶ò‡¶ü‡¶®‡¶æ: ‡¶Ü‡ßü ‡¶π‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶æ‡¶∏‡•§
- ‡¶Ö‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶∂‡¶®: Debit Service Charge Account.

| ‡¶Ö‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶â‡¶®‡ßç‡¶ü            | Debit (‡¶°‡ßá‡¶¨‡¶ø‡¶ü) | Credit (‡¶ï‡ßç‡¶∞‡ßá‡¶°‡¶ø‡¶ü) |
| --------------------- | ------------- | ---------------- |
| Service Charge Income | 500           | ‚Äî                |



---

### ‡ß™. Expense (‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡ßü) ‚Äî ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶Ç‡¶ï‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶™‡¶ï‡ßá‡¶ü ‡¶•‡ßá‡¶ï‡ßá ‡¶Ø‡¶æ ‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶ö‡ßç‡¶õ‡ßá

‡¶≤‡¶ú‡¶ø‡¶ï: 
‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡ßü ‡¶¨‡¶æ ‡¶ñ‡¶∞‡¶ö ‡¶Ü‡¶≤‡ßç‡¶ü‡¶ø‡¶Æ‡ßá‡¶ü‡¶≤‡¶ø ‡¶∏‡¶Æ‡ßç‡¶™‡¶¶‡ßá‡¶∞ (Cash) ‡¶¨‡¶ø‡¶™‡¶∞‡ßÄ‡¶§ ‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶ú ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡ßá‡•§ ‡¶§‡¶æ‡¶á ‡¶ñ‡¶∞‡¶ö ‡¶¨‡¶æ‡ßú‡¶≤‡ßá ‡¶∏‡ßá‡¶ü‡¶æ ‡¶∏‡¶Æ‡ßç‡¶™‡¶¶‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶Æ‡¶§‡ßã‡¶á Debit ‡¶π‡ßü‡•§

- ‡¶¨‡¶æ‡¶∏‡ßç‡¶§‡¶¨ ‡¶â‡¶¶‡¶æ‡¶π‡¶∞‡¶£: ‡¶Æ‡¶æ‡¶∏ ‡¶∂‡ßá‡¶∑‡ßá ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶Ç‡¶ï ‡¶§‡¶æ‡¶∞ ‡¶∏‡ßç‡¶ü‡¶æ‡¶´‡¶¶‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶∏‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶≤‡¶æ‡¶∞‡¶ø ‡¶¶‡¶ø‡¶≤‡ßã ‡ßß‡ß¶ ‡¶≤‡¶ï‡ßç‡¶∑ ‡¶ü‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶æ‡•§
- ‡¶ò‡¶ü‡¶®‡¶æ: ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡ßü ‡¶¨‡¶æ ‡¶ñ‡¶∞‡¶ö ‡¶¨‡ßÉ‡¶¶‡ßç‡¶ß‡¶ø‡•§
- ‡¶Ö‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶∂‡¶®: Debit Salary Expense Account.

| ‡¶Ö‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶â‡¶®‡ßç‡¶ü     | Debit (‡¶°‡ßá‡¶¨‡¶ø‡¶ü) | Credit (‡¶ï‡ßç‡¶∞‡ßá‡¶°‡¶ø‡¶ü) |
| -------------- | ------------- | ---------------- |
| Salary Expense | 10,00,000     | ‚Äî                |
| Cash           | ‚Äî             | 10,00,000        |



- ‡¶π‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶æ‡¶∏ ‡¶™‡¶æ‡¶ì‡ßü‡¶æ‡¶∞ ‡¶â‡¶¶‡¶æ‡¶π‡¶∞‡¶£: ‡¶Ö‡¶ó‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶ø‡¶Æ ‡¶¨‡¶æ‡ßú‡¶ø ‡¶≠‡¶æ‡ßú‡¶æ ‡¶¶‡ßá‡¶ì‡ßü‡¶æ ‡¶π‡ßü‡ßá‡¶õ‡¶ø‡¶≤, ‡¶∏‡ßá‡¶ü‡¶æ ‡¶è‡¶ñ‡¶® ‡¶Æ‡¶æ‡¶∏ ‡¶∂‡ßá‡¶∑‡ßá ‡¶Ö‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶°‡¶ú‡¶æ‡¶∏‡ßç‡¶ü ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡¶æ ‡¶π‡¶≤‡ßã‡•§
- ‡¶ò‡¶ü‡¶®‡¶æ: ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡ßü ‡¶π‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶æ‡¶∏‡•§
- ‡¶Ö‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶∂‡¶®: Credit Expense Account.

| ‡¶Ö‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶â‡¶®‡ßç‡¶ü      | Debit (‡¶°‡ßá‡¶¨‡¶ø‡¶ü) | Credit (‡¶ï‡ßç‡¶∞‡ßá‡¶°‡¶ø‡¶ü) |
| --------------- | ------------- | ---------------- |
| Expense Account | ‚Äî             | 10,000           |



############################################### Double-Entry Table simple EXAMPLE in CBS  ###############################################


CBS/Core Banking System-‡¶è ‡¶°‡¶æ‡¶¨‡¶≤ ‡¶è‡¶®‡ßç‡¶ü‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶ø ‡¶ï‡ßÄ‡¶≠‡¶æ‡¶¨‡ßá ‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶ú ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡ßá‚Äî‡¶è‡¶ï‡¶¶‡¶Æ ‡¶∏‡¶´‡¶ü‡¶ì‡ßü‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶∞/‡¶°‡ßá‡¶≠‡ßá‡¶≤‡¶™‡¶Æ‡ßá‡¶®‡ßç‡¶ü ‡¶≠‡¶ø‡¶â‡¶§‡ßá‡•§


üî∂ Step-1: Double-Entry Table

### Example-A: Cusotmer Cash Deposit (‡ß≥5,000)
------------------------------------------------
| Account Head                 | Debit | Credit |
| ---------------------------- | ----- | ------ |
| Cash (Asset)                 | 5,000 | ‚Äî      |
| Customer Deposit (Liability) | ‚Äî     | 5,000  |
------------------------------------------------

### Example-B: Customer Withdraws ‡ß≥1,000
------------------------------------------------
| Account Head                 | Debit | Credit |
| ---------------------------- | ----- | ------ |
| Customer Deposit (Liability) | 1,000 | ‚Äî      |
| Cash (Asset)                 | ‚Äî     | 1,000  |
------------------------------------------------

üî∂ Step-2: CBS / Ledger Posting (Real Banking Logic)
‡¶è‡¶ñ‡¶® ‡¶è‡¶ü‡¶æ‡¶ï‡ßá Core Banking System (CBS) ‡¶è‡¶∞ ‡¶≠‡¶æ‡¶∑‡¶æ‡ßü ‡¶¶‡ßá‡¶ñ‡¶ø

## üßæ Ledger Structure (Simple)
### 1Ô∏è‚É£ Account Table (Master)
--------------------------------------------------
| account_id | account_name          | type      |
| ---------- | --------------------- | --------- |
| 101        | Cash                  | ASSET     |
| 201        | Customer Deposit      | LIABILITY |
| 301        | Service Charge Income | INCOME    |
| 401        | Salary Expense        | EXPENSE   |
--------------------------------------------------

## üßæ Transaction Table
------------------------------------------
| txn_id | debit_ac | credit_ac | amount |
| ------ | -------- | --------- | ------ |
| TXN001 | 101      | 201       | 5000   |
| TXN001 | 201      | 101       | 1000   |
------------------------------------------




############################################### ADVANCED EXAMPLE in CBS  ###############################################


## 1) CBS-‡¶è Double Entry ‡¶Æ‡¶æ‡¶®‡ßá ‡¶ï‡ßÄ (Software View)

CBS-‡¶è ‡¶™‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶§‡¶ø‡¶ü‡¶æ ‡¶ü‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶æ‡¶®‡¶ú‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶∂‡¶® ‚Äú‡¶è‡¶ï‡¶ü‡¶æ ‡¶∞‡ßã‚Äù ‡¶®‡¶æ‚Äî
‡¶è‡¶ü‡¶æ ‡¶Ü‡¶∏‡¶≤‡ßá ‡¶è‡¶ï‡¶ü‡¶æ ‡¶≠‡¶æ‡¶â‡¶ö‡¶æ‡¶∞ (Voucher / Journal), 
‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶∞ ‡¶≠‡¶ø‡¶§‡¶∞‡ßá ‡¶•‡¶æ‡¶ï‡ßá ‡¶è‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶ß‡¶ø‡¶ï ‡¶≤‡ßá‡¶ú‡¶æ‡¶∞ ‡¶≤‡¶æ‡¶á‡¶® (Dr/Cr lines)‡•§

‚úÖ ‡¶®‡¶ø‡ßü‡¶Æ: Voucher-level ‡¶è Total Debit = Total Credit
‚úÖ ‡¶∏‡¶¨‡¶∏‡¶Æ‡ßü ‚ÄúBalanced voucher‚Äù ‡¶®‡¶æ ‡¶π‡¶≤‡ßá Post ‡¶π‡¶¨‡ßá ‡¶®‡¶æ

---

## 2) Banking Ledger Architecture (Simple)

‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶Ç‡¶ï‡ßá ‡¶∏‡¶æ‡¶ß‡¶æ‡¶∞‡¶£‡¶§ 2 ‡¶≤‡ßá‡ßü‡¶æ‡¶∞ ‡¶•‡¶æ‡¶ï‡ßá:

### A) Sub-ledger (Customer-level)

- Customer Deposit Account (Savings/Current)
- Loan Account
- Card account, etc.

### B) General Ledger (GL) (Bank-level)

- Cash in Vault
- Bank (Nostro) / Settlement
- Customer Deposits (Liability GL)
- Loans & Advances (Asset GL)
- Interest/Profit Income
- Fees Income
- Expense

üëâ Customer transaction ‡¶π‡¶≤‡ßá ‡¶™‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶æ‡ßü‡¶á ‡¶∏‡¶æ‡¶¨-‡¶≤‡ßá‡¶ú‡¶æ‡¶∞ + GL‚Äî‡¶¶‡ßÅ‡¶ü‡ßã‡¶§‡ßá‡¶á ‡¶™‡ßã‡¶∏‡ßç‡¶ü ‡¶π‡ßü‡•§

---

## 3) Posting Flow (Step-by-step)

1. Validate (amount>0, account active, limits, AML, etc.)
2. Build Voucher (lines ‡¶§‡ßà‡¶∞‡¶ø)
3. Balance Check (sumDr == sumCr)
4. Persist as Pending
5. Atomic Post (DB Transaction)
   - Insert Voucher header
   - Insert Voucher lines
   - Update account balances (or store as running balance)
6. Mark Posted + generate reference number
7. Return receipt

---

## 4) Common Banking Transactions (Dr/Cr Examples)

### ‚úÖ (A) Customer Deposit: ‡¶ó‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶æ‡¶π‡¶ï 10,000 ‡¶ü‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶æ ‡¶ï‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶∂‡ßá ‡¶ú‡¶Æ‡¶æ ‡¶¶‡¶ø‡¶≤

Bank view:

- Cash (Asset) Dr 10,000
- Customer Deposits GL (Liability) Cr 10,000
- (Sub-ledger) Customer deposit account balance ‡¶¨‡¶æ‡ßú‡¶¨‡ßá

Voucher Lines

- Dr: GL_CASH
- Cr: GL_CUST_DEPOSITS
- Subledger: CustomerAccount +10,000

---

### ‚úÖ (B) Withdrawal: ‡¶ó‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶æ‡¶π‡¶ï 2,000 ‡¶ü‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶æ ‡¶§‡ßÅ‡¶≤‡¶≤

- Customer Deposits GL Dr 2,000 (liability ‡¶ï‡¶Æ‡ßá)
- Cash Cr 2,000 (asset ‡¶ï‡¶Æ‡ßá)
- Sub-ledger: CustomerAccount -2,000

---

### ‚úÖ (C) Transfer: A ‡¶•‡ßá‡¶ï‡ßá B-‡¶ï‡ßá 500 ‡¶ü‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶æ

- Customer Deposit (A) Cr 500 (A ‡¶ï‡¶Æ‡¶¨‡ßá) ‚Äî ‡¶∏‡¶æ‡¶¨-‡¶≤‡ßá‡¶ú‡¶æ‡¶∞
- Customer Deposit (B) Dr 500 (B ‡¶¨‡¶æ‡ßú‡¶¨‡ßá) ‚Äî ‡¶∏‡¶æ‡¶¨-‡¶≤‡ßá‡¶ú‡¶æ‡¶∞

GL-‡¶è ‡¶Ö‡¶®‡ßá‡¶ï ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶Ç‡¶ï‡ßá netting ‡¶π‡ßü, ‡¶Ö‡¶•‡¶¨‡¶æ internal clearing ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶¨‡¶π‡¶æ‡¶∞ ‡¶π‡ßü‡•§ ‡¶∏‡¶π‡¶ú‡¶≠‡¶æ‡¶¨‡ßá:

- Dr: Customer Deposits (B)
- Cr: Customer Deposits (A)
  (‡¶è‡¶ü‡¶æ ‡¶¨‡¶æ‡¶∏‡ßç‡¶§‡¶¨‡ßá ‚Äúsame GL‚Äù ‡¶π‡¶≤‡ßá sub-ledger lines ‡¶¶‡¶ø‡ßü‡ßá‡¶á handle ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡¶æ ‡¶π‡ßü)

---

## 5) .NET Core-‡¶è Ledger Posting (Practical Design)

### Core Entities (Minimum)

VoucherHeader

- VoucherId, Date, Type (Deposit/Withdraw/Transfer), ReferenceNo, Status

VoucherLine

- LineId, VoucherId
- AccountType: GL / SUBLEDGER
- AccountId (GLCode or CustomerAccountId)
- DrAmount, CrAmount
- Narrative

AccountBalance

- AccountId, Balance (‡¶¨‡¶æ ledger-balance, available-balance)

---

## 6) Database Table Sketch (MySQL compatible)

```sql
CREATE TABLE voucher_headers (
  voucher_id BIGINT PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT,
  txn_date DATETIME NOT NULL,
  txn_type VARCHAR(30) NOT NULL,
  reference_no VARCHAR(50) UNIQUE,
  status ENUM('PENDING','POSTED','REVERSED') DEFAULT 'PENDING',
  created_at DATETIME DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE voucher_lines (
  line_id BIGINT PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT,
  voucher_id BIGINT NOT NULL,
  account_type ENUM('GL','SUB') NOT NULL,
  account_id VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  dr DECIMAL(18,2) DEFAULT 0,
  cr DECIMAL(18,2) DEFAULT 0,
  narrative VARCHAR(255),
  FOREIGN KEY (voucher_id) REFERENCES voucher_headers(voucher_id)
);

CREATE TABLE account_balances (
  account_id VARCHAR(50) PRIMARY KEY,
  balance DECIMAL(18,2) NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
  updated_at DATETIME DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);
```

---

## 7) Posting Service Logic (C# ‚Äì Clean & Exam-friendly)

Key point: DB transaction ‡¶õ‡¶æ‡ßú‡¶æ ‡¶™‡ßã‡¶∏‡ßç‡¶ü‡¶ø‡¶Ç ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡¶¨‡ßá‡¶® ‡¶®‡¶æ‡•§

```csharp
public class PostingService
{
    private readonly AppDbContext _db;

    public PostingService(AppDbContext db) => _db = db;

    public async Task<long> PostAsync(VoucherHeader header, List<VoucherLine> lines)
    {
        // 1) Balance check
        var totalDr = lines.Sum(l => l.Dr);
        var totalCr = lines.Sum(l => l.Cr);
        if (totalDr != totalCr) throw new Exception("Voucher is not balanced!");

        using var tx = await _db.Database.BeginTransactionAsync();

        // 2) Save header
        header.Status = "PENDING";
        _db.VoucherHeaders.Add(header);
        await _db.SaveChangesAsync();

        // 3) Save lines
        foreach (var l in lines)
        {
            l.VoucherId = header.VoucherId;
            _db.VoucherLines.Add(l);

            // 4) Update balance (simple model)
            // balance += Dr - Cr
            var bal = await _db.AccountBalances.FindAsync(l.AccountId);
            if (bal == null)
            {
                bal = new AccountBalance { AccountId = l.AccountId, Balance = 0 };
                _db.AccountBalances.Add(bal);
            }
            bal.Balance += (l.Dr - l.Cr);
        }

        // 5) Mark posted
        header.Status = "POSTED";
        header.ReferenceNo = $"TXN-{header.VoucherId:000000}";
        await _db.SaveChangesAsync();

        await tx.CommitAsync();
        return header.VoucherId;
    }
}
```

---

## 8) Deposit Example (Controller ‡¶•‡ßá‡¶ï‡ßá Call)

```csharp
[HttpPost]
public async Task<IActionResult> CashDeposit(string customerAccId, decimal amount)
{
    // Build voucher
    var header = new VoucherHeader {
        TxnDate = DateTime.Now,
        TxnType = "CASH_DEPOSIT"
    };

    var lines = new List<VoucherLine>
    {
        // GL Cash Dr
        new VoucherLine { AccountType="GL", AccountId="GL_CASH", Dr=amount, Cr=0, Narrative="Cash received" },

        // GL Customer Deposit Liability Cr
        new VoucherLine { AccountType="GL", AccountId="GL_CUST_DEPOSITS", Dr=0, Cr=amount, Narrative="Customer deposit liability" },

        // Sub-ledger customer account Dr (optional: depending on your design)
        new VoucherLine { AccountType="SUB", AccountId=customerAccId, Dr=amount, Cr=0, Narrative="Customer balance increase" }
    };

    // ‚ö†Ô∏è ‡¶Ø‡¶¶‡¶ø SUB ‡¶≤‡¶æ‡¶á‡¶® ‡¶Ø‡ßã‡¶ó ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡ßá‡¶®, ‡¶§‡¶æ‡¶π‡¶≤‡ßá GL side-‡¶è matching design ‡¶∞‡¶æ‡¶ñ‡¶¨‡ßá‡¶® (‡¶®‡¶æ ‡¶π‡¶≤‡ßá triple-effect ‡¶π‡¶¨‡ßá)
    // Alternative: SUB balance update separate, but voucher lines only GL.

    var id = await _postingService.PostAsync(header, lines);
    return Ok(new { voucherId = id });
}
```

> ‡¶®‡ßã‡¶ü: ‡¶¨‡¶æ‡¶∏‡ßç‡¶§‡¶¨ CBS-‡¶è ‡¶∏‡¶æ‡¶ß‡¶æ‡¶∞‡¶£‡¶§ voucher-lines-‡¶è GL lines ‡¶•‡¶æ‡¶ï‡ßá, ‡¶Ü‡¶∞ customer balance update ‡¶π‡ßü sub-ledger posting ‡¶π‡¶ø‡¶∏‡ßá‡¶¨‡ßá‡•§ 
‡¶Ü‡¶™‡¶®‡¶ø ‡¶ö‡¶æ‡¶á‡¶≤‡ßá ‡¶Ü‡¶Æ‡¶ø ‚ÄúBest practice architecture‚Äù ‡¶¶‡ßá‡¶ñ‡¶ø‡ßü‡ßá ‡¶¶‡ßá‡¶¨ (GL-only voucher + subledger posting table)‡•§

---

## 9) Best Practice (Real Banking Style) ‚Äî ‡¶ñ‡ßÅ‡¶¨ ‡¶ó‡ßÅ‡¶∞‡ßÅ‡¶§‡ßç‡¶¨‡¶™‡ßÇ‡¶∞‡ßç‡¶£

‚úÖ VoucherLines = only GL
‚úÖ Sub-ledger posting = separate table (customer account + amount, reference voucher id)
‡¶ï‡¶æ‡¶∞‡¶£:

- GL audit strong ‡¶π‡ßü
- Subledger reconciliation ‡¶∏‡¶π‡¶ú ‡¶π‡ßü
- Customer statement ‡¶¶‡ßç‡¶∞‡ßÅ‡¶§ ‡¶§‡ßà‡¶∞‡¶ø ‡¶π‡ßü

---

## 10) ‡¶Ü‡¶™‡¶®‡¶ø ‡¶ï‡ßã‡¶®‡¶ü‡¶æ ‡¶ö‡¶æ‡¶®?

‡¶Ü‡¶™‡¶®‡¶ø ‡¶¨‡¶≤‡¶≤‡ßá‡¶á ‡¶Ü‡¶Æ‡¶ø ‡¶è‡¶ï‡¶¶‡¶Æ ‡¶Ü‡¶™‡¶®‡¶æ‡¶∞ ‡¶™‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶ú‡ßá‡¶ï‡ßç‡¶ü ‡¶∏‡ßç‡¶ü‡¶æ‡¶á‡¶≤‡ßá ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡ßá ‡¶¶‡¶ø‡¶ö‡ßç‡¶õ‡¶ø:

1. GL-only Voucher + SubledgerPosting (CBS-accurate)
2. ‡¶è‡¶ï‡¶ü‡¶æ Full Flow: Deposit + Withdraw + Transfer + Reversal (undo)
3. Islamic banking style: Profit posting (Murabaha/Installment split: Principal/Profit)

‡¶Ü‡¶™‡¶®‡¶ø ‡¶ï‡ßã‡¶®‡¶ü‡¶æ ‡¶Ü‡¶ó‡ßá ‡¶ö‡¶æ‡¶®‚Äî(1) CBS accurate model ‡¶®‡¶æ‡¶ï‡¶ø (2) ‡¶è‡¶ñ‡¶®‡¶á Transfer + Reversal implement?







.
